2. Waste Management: A feature for managing the waste generated in the village can be added. It can include a system for garbage collection and disposal, and recycling of the waste materials. The system can also include a mechanism for incentivizing the villagers to properly dispose of the waste.
3. Smart Grid: A smart grid system can be implemented to manage the power distribution in the village. It can include monitoring of the power usage in the village and optimizing the power distribution to avoid blackouts. The system can also include a mechanism for incentivizing the villagers to use electricity efficiently.
4. Education Management: A feature for managing the education system in the village can be added. It can include monitoring of attendance of students and teachers, scheduling of classes, and an online platform for education materials. The system can also include a mechanism for incentivizing the students to attend school regularly.
5. Healthcare Management: A feature for managing the healthcare system in the village can be added. It can include monitoring of health parameters of the villagers, scheduling of health checkups, and an online platform for booking appointments with doctors. The system can also include a mechanism for incentivizing the villagers to maintain a healthy lifestyle.

